                    },
                    {
                      "amount": 0,
                      "display_style": "card",
                      "ep_id": 2125,
                      "icon_url": "https://bbs.hoyolab.com/hoyowiki/picture/enemy/Thundercraven Rifthound_icon.png",
                      "name": "Гончая Разрыва: Громоед",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    },
                    {
                      "amount": 0,
                      "display_style": "card",
                      "ep_id": 2123,
                      "icon_url": "https://bbs.hoyolab.com/hoyowiki/picture/enemy/Rockfond Rifthound_icon.png",
                      "name": "Гончая Разрыва: Камнегрыз",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    },
                    {
                      "amount": 0,
                      "display_style": "card",
                      "ep_id": 2247,
                      "icon_url": "https://bbs.hoyolab.com/hoyowiki/picture/enemy/Golden Wolflord_icon.png",
                      "name": "Золотой волчий вожак",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    },
                    {
                      "amount": 0,
                      "display_style": "card",
                      "ep_id": 4306,
                      "icon_url": "https://upload-static.hoyoverse.com/hoyolab-wiki/2023/09/10/77454259/5297fd201cef47a3124d0d2c95f8d6db_4814893845746431355.png",
                      "name": "Enigmatic Page (V)",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:rgb(255, 255, 255)"
                      ],
                      "text": "Elynas's Death and Melusines’ Birth",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "level": 1,
                  "type": "heading"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Elynas appeared in Fontaine during the Cataclysm 500 years ago. Its existence poisoned the water and land, so the Fontaine fleet, led by Basil Elton on her ship Sponsian, was sent to protect Fontaine from Elynas. They chased the Abyssal beast for about 35 days, constantly fighting other Abyssal monsters. When most of the fleet's ships were sunk, the Sponsian flagship was significantly damaged, and Elynas himself was wounded, the Sponsian overtook the beast. As a result of the battle, the ship was split in two, and one half was stuck in Elynas's body. The second half can still be seen in the waters near Elton Trench, floating like a ghost.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "alignment": "left",
                      "type": "custom_image",
                      "url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/02/22/237301566/acb85bf4ad0cb25cb352b5612b60ea22_6428975139913856858.png"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Realizing that he only brought destruction and suffering, Elynas decided to stop fighting and die. He was filled with sorrow, but yet was glad it was all over. Although his body and heart were petrified, he still retained consciousness and was therefore glad when people appeared in his body more than 400 years ago. It was Jakob Ingold and Rene de Petrichor, who used the flesh and blood of Elynas to research and improve the powers of the first Neohuman Jakob. But one day, many other creatures appeared in his body, including metal machines, a spirit of the primordial waters and other people. There was a battle and an explosion inside Elynas's body that damaged his flesh, and from these wounds the Melusines, Elynas's children, were born. Each Melusine was born with a shard of broken Mek, so they began considering these objects as their \"token,\" which must be protected. To protect himself and his daughters, Elynas created the Breacher Primuses, unusual living creatures that are neither plants nor animals. They were less intellectually developed than the Melusines themselves, but some Melusines began to care for them as their pets.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "italic"
                      ],
                      "text": "\"I was so overjoyed, for they were beautiful and intelligent. Also, that was when I realized that I could do more than destroy — I could bring beautiful new life into this world.\"",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Elynas loved his daughters so much and considered them beautiful. He often talked to them and taught them how to build a home for themselves so that they might grow up well. Then, there was happiness and liveliness everywhere. The Melusines founded the Merusea village inside the Elynas's body, in which they lived for many years. Centuries later, almost all Melusines, except one, Mamere, lost the opportunity to communicate with their \"Father\" and forgot about him. Some began to consider him a caring \"mother,\" while others simply do not remember their origins.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:rgb(255, 215, 128)"
                      ],
                      "text": "Related Entries:",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
