                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:rgb(255, 255, 255)"
                      ],
                      "text": "Ancient Colors",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "level": 1,
                  "type": "heading"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "alignment": "left",
                      "type": "custom_image",
                      "url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/02/22/237301566/547c45ab9dfa0ea2c8fe583fa0f6df3b_7560227245124190085.png"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Elynas only met two people who could resist his poison: Jakob Ingold and the Traveler. While he was glad to help Jakob as he fueled his powers with the Elynas’s flesh and blood, he did not want his heart to be revived again. Elynas was afraid that his daughters would die, and their small houses would be destroyed, so he was grateful to the Traveler for stopping Jakob. In gratitude, he asked his daughter Mamere to paint a picture with his blood, which allowed Elynas to meet the Traveler. As a farewell, he conveyed a message to Mamere and wished to meet the Traveler again.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "italic"
                      ],
                      "text": "Could you tell Mamere... Hmm, what to say… How about this, then? \"Your paintings are very beautiful. I love you, and I'm so very proud of you.\" Ah, right, and \"please get along with your sisters — they love you very much as well.\" Alright then, thank you! Honestly, it was great meeting you. Someday, I hope that I'll be able to traverse this world without fear of causing harm or death to others. When that time comes, I'll be sure to show you what I really look like!",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:rgb(255, 215, 128)"
                      ],
